title: gibson_les_paul
body:
Solid body [[electric guitar]] manufactured by [[gibson_brands_inc|Gibson]] since 1952, designed with input by famed jazz guitarist Les Paul whose name ended up as the name of the [[guitar]] itself, work and prototypes commenced in 1950, with 1951 prototypes being strikingly similar to the final product until its introduction in 1952. The Les Paul eventually caught big success in a seemingly endless array of genres, pinning it as one of the most well known and popular guitars along with its contemporaries, the [[Fender Telecaster]] and [[Fender Stratocaster]]. It's similarly been used by musicians far and wide, including [[Slash (Musician)|Slash]], Joe Perry and James Dean Bradfield among others.

The Les Paul also holds a strong cult following in Japan. Within anime and manga, [[K-On!]]'s [[Hirasawa Yui]] is most associated with the Les Paul, using a Cherry Sunburst Les Paul Standard (now Traditional). Other prominent characters include [[iDOLMASTER Million Live!]]'s [[Julia (Idolmaster)|Julia]] using a TV Yellow Les Paul Special, [[Bang Dream!]]'s [[Mitake Ran]] with a red Les Paul copy, and [[Bocchi The Rock!]]'s [[Gotoh Hitori]] with a black Les Paul custom.

Original Les Pauls were released with goldtop finishes, P90 ("soapbar") pickups and either stopbars or tailpieces. Prominent Gibson versions of the Les Paul include:
* Standard, most famous example in anime being Hirasawa Yui's model.
* Junior/Special, lighter glossier model with soapbar pickups with the Junior only sporting a single pickup, most commonly seen being used by iDOLMASTER's Julia.
* DC/DC Lite, a double-cutaway version, famously used in Japan by [[B'z]] guitarist [[Matsumoto Takahiro (B'z)|Matsumoto Takahiro]]. (post #2361213)
* Custom, featuring gold hardware, most commonly seen in either black or white. (post #1867738)

title: fender_stratocaster
body:
Solid body [[electric guitar]], made and produced by American [[instrument]] maker [[fender_musical_instruments_corporation|Fender]] since 1954.

Designs and prototypes were made around 1953 which were subsequently set into production without minor changes including colors and finishes. Noted and recognised as a revolutionary and innovative guitar at the time, the Stratocaster quickly gained worldwide renown and became one of the most popular electric guitars in history, with its basic design still being used and modified by many other guitar manufacturers to this day. The [[Fender Stratocaster]], alongside the [[Fender Telecaster]], have been used across a wide range of musical genres by countless musicians, with the Strat being associated with legendary guitarists like [[Yngwie Malmsteen]], [[Eric Clapton]], and [[Jimi Hendrix]].

In Japanese animation, [[Iwasawa Masami]] of [[Angel Beats!]] and [[Hanazono Tae]] of [[Bang Dream!]] are two of the most prominent players, the latter using a Stratocaster-style guitar made by [[ESP Guitars]].

Features a unique contour body with double cutaway, triple single-coil setup as standard, three control knobs and tremolo bridge. Akin to the Telecaster, an endless amount of versions and configurations exist, but the base design always stays the same.

title: duplicate
body:
A post that is the same or inferior to an already existing post. This tag only applies to inferior posts that were uploaded [b]after[/b] an already existing identical post.

Duplicates should not be confused for the following:

* [[image sample]], an image typically used by sites to load images faster.
* [[md5 mismatch]], an post that has a different md5 from the file at the source.
* [[revision]], a post that has been revised by the artist from a previous version.
* [[variant set]], posts with a similar base, but non-trivial differences.
* [[scan]], a post that has been scanned from another source.

A few cases where the tag applies:

* Images with [[pixel-perfect duplicate|identical pixel data]], but different metadata.
* Lower resolution versions of the same post.
* [[Resized]] posts. Note that duplicate resized posts should not be tagged with [[md5 mismatch]].
* Images of generally lower quality; often a result of [[jpeg artifacts]].
* [[Has bad revision|Bad revisions]].

Before you upload something, check if it has already been uploaded by using the "IQDB image search":http://danbooru.iqdb.org/ or the "Find similar" button.

Both duplicates and [[pixel-perfect duplicate]]s must be tagged manually. There is no automated system in place to accurately tag duplicates given how easy it is to confuse them for the above (with exception to [[image sample]]s where the original is already uploaded). [[Pixel-perfect duplicate]]s are no longer automatically tagged; refer to its wiki on how to check for them.

h6. Notes:

* [b]Do not flag a duplicate post for deletion if your only reason is that the post is a duplicate.[/b] Parent them to the superior image instead.
* Don't add the duplicate tag on posts with visual differences ([[variant_set|variants]], [[revision|revisions]], [[textless version]]s etc.).
* Avoid uploading visually identical posts.
** Check for differences with "DuplicateBooru":https://duplicatebooru.zipfiled.info/ if you are unable to confirm with your own eyes.
* Filesize alone does not determine the superiority of an image. For example, for a jpeg with the same resolution as another, the one with less artifacts is superior.

h4. Related tags

Not to be confused with [[multiple sources]], although they may overlap sometimes.

* [[multiple sources]] is about outside sources -- it means that multiple copies are available outside Danbooru.
* [[duplicate]] is about Danbooru -- it means that we have multiple copies of the same image.

h4. See also

* [[help:upload]]
* [[help:image source]]

h4. External Links

* "How can I tell exactly what changed between two images?":[https://photo.stackexchange.com/a/11739]
* "Diffchecker":https://www.diffchecker.com/image-diff [tn]Online compare images[/tn]
* "ImageMagick":https://www.imagemagick.org/ [tn]Multitool with "compare":https://imagemagick.org/script/compare.php function[/tn]
* "XnView MP":https://www.xnview.com/en/xnviewmp [tn]Image viewer. Support EXIF, IPTC, XMP metadata[/tn]
* "ExifTool":https://exiftool.org/ [tn]Command-line application for work with metadata[/tn]

"Aoqun" is a type of [[Hanfu]], where the upper garment is worn over the [[skirt]], untucked, a style that emerged in [[China]] as early as the Spring and Autumn period and became more common during the Wei, Jin, and Northern and Southern dynasties, spreading to [[Japan]] during the Asuka period.

Some aoqun have a very long upper garment, where you can only see the skirt near the bottom of the outfit, but more common is aoqun where they are about equal in length. The styles differ greatly but still fall under the aoqun category if theres a skirt and an untucked upper garment. 

[[Ruqun]] is the opposite; hanfu where the top is tucked into the skirt.

title: gangsta_hold
body:
[[Holding gun|Holding a gun]] sideways. So named for the gangsters who supposedly demonstrate this technique in gunfights. Frequently combined with [[dual wielding]].

Shooting a gun in this way has no practical benefit under most circumstances and makes proper aiming very difficult. However, the style has become somewhat popular in rap culture and among street criminals (who do not often use the gun sight) due to its portrayal in U.S. film and television since the 1990s, which in turn was inspired by Hong Kong action cinema beginning in the '70s and '80s. It is believed that Hong Kong actors needed to hold their guns in this way because some Chinese-made automatics couldn't eject shell casings reliably.

It is also known that this type of grip was sometimes used during the Chinese Civil War of the '30s and '40s with full-auto versions of the top-ejecting [[Mauser C96|Mauser C96 "Broomhandle"]] pistol, which had an extremely high rate of fire and significant muzzle climb when fired normally. When held in what's now known as gangsta style and fired, the muzzle would instead "climb" sideways and thus sweep across everything in front of the shooter. A similar technique was sometimes used with submachine guns during World War II, but as they were significantly bulkier and heavier than the C96 it was considerably more awkward.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Side grip":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Side_grip

The story revolves around a shy girl named [[Asai Mugi]] who is unsure of what club to join in her school, but before she knows it she gets dragged into the Drama Research Society and becomes a member. The manga was first serialized in the Japanese seinen manga magazine Comic High! on March 22, 2004, and is published by Futabasha. title: saxophone
body:
A musical instrument that is popular in jazz, classical, and funk music. Comes in four popular sizes (listed from smallest to largest): soprano, alto, tenor, and baritone. (Smaller and larger variations than the soprano and baritone exist, but they are very rarely used.)

[[alto saxophone|Alto]]: Most commonly used and often in small jazz groups as well as large ensembles. Most distinct feature is that the neck is straight where the mouthpiece is attached. Convenient in size for generally all player heights, standing or sitting. 

 [[tenor saxophone|Tenor]]: Slightly larger with the physical distinction being the curved neck. Second most common and can be just as essential as the alto. 

 [[baritone saxophone|Baritone]]: Largest and with a deep bass-like sound, the neck has a complete loop. The size and the weight is considerably harder to maneuver than the rest. They are less common than the prior two, but can be still seen in large wind ensembles and medium to large jazz groups to provide bass depth.

[[soprano saxophone|Soprano]]: The look and posture it is held is almost exactly like a [[clarinet|clarinet]]. Mostly used as a solo instrument in classical or orchestral environments, or in a saxophone quartet.

title: where_is_poor_(meme)
body:
A [[meme]] based on a [[politics|political]] cartoon depicting an [[obese]] man looking into a pair of [[binoculars]] while asking "Where are the poor?" His large stomach blocks his view of a starving man below him. The edit that popularized the political cartoon as a meme changed to the text to state "Where is poor?"

On March 3rd, 2025, "Twitter user @lilchiikawa_":https://twitter.com/lilchiikawa_/status/1896693852435886433 posted a redrawn version of the meme featuring the characters [[Chiikawa_(Character)|]] and [[Usagi_(Chiikawa)|]] from the series [[Chiikawa]]. This version of the meme went viral, causing several artworks inspired by it to be made. Though in this version, the second, smaller character is often being covered by [[gigantic breasts]] of the first character instead.

h4. Examples
* !asset #25240483: Original political cartoon
* !asset #25240484: Popularized meme edit
* !asset #25240486: [[Chiikawa]] version

h4. External links

title: venus_a
body:
A [[mecha|mech]] appearing in the [[Mazinger_(series)|Mazinger]] series.

Initially set to appear in the original [[Mazinger Z]] anime as an upgrade and replacement to [[yumi_sayaka|Sayaka Yumi's]] [[aphrodai_a|Aphrodite A]]. It ended up not appearing in favor of [[dianan_a|Diana A]].

However, it does appear in the original manga following Aphrodite's  destruction and is piloted by Sayaka. It was designed by [[Doctor Morimori|the]] [[doctor_sewashi|three]] [[doctor_nossori|scientists]] at the Photon Power Laboratory to invoke Sayaka's appearance.

It would eventually make its anime debut in the [[Great Mazinger]] anime. In this continuity, 
it was designed by [[Kabuto Kenzo]] and is instead piloted by [[Honoo Jun]]. Additionally, its colors were altered slightly to better resemble Jun rather than Sayaka.

Future reprints of the original Mazinger Z manga as well other media based on it would tweak Sayaka's version of the mech to less closely resemble Jun's (despite Sayaka's being the original design). Oddly, Sayaka's Venus A's redesign more closely resembles Jun when she dons her [[mecha_pilot_suit|pilot suit]] than it does Sayaka.

title: locacaca
body:
The Locacaca is an enigmatic species of plant featured in the eighth part of the [[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]] series, [[JoJolion]]. Although introduced seemingly without much importance, it becomes central to the plot of JoJolion as the part develops, with multiple sides seeking and preserving the plant for their own purposes.

Locacaca [[tree]]s are small trees with tubular and crenelated trunks, small enough to be hidden in a [[suitcase]]. At the top of a Locacaca tree is a [[crown]] of leaves. Thin, thorny, leafless branches grow out of the trunk, and they rotate perpendicularly as they grow fruit. The Locacaca [[fruit]]s themselves are ovoid and covered with small points of flesh, and the leaves attached to the fruit resemble fig tree leaves. The interior of the fruit is compartmentalized, like a citrus fruit. The fruit tastes of bitter fig.

When she lets down her hair, it gets slightly wavy and reaches the edge of her face.

Her usual outfit is composed of a [[cropped shirt|cropped]] [[white shirt|white top]] with [[puffy sleeves]] that reach her elbows and dark [[green shorts]] with a [[white belt]]. She additionally wears [[white boots|white]] [[knee boots|over-the-knee boots]] and white [[bracelet|bracelets]].

When performing spells as a mage, Kanne uses a long, straight [[mage staff|staff]] with a jeweled center and three prongs that are reminiscent of crystals.

title: space_ghost_coast_to_coast
body:
Space Ghost Coast to Coast is an American adult animated comedy late-night talk show created by Mike Lazzo for [[Cartoon Network]] and starring a re-imagined version of the cast of the 1960s Hanna-Barbera cartoon [[Space Ghost (series)|]], hosted by [[Space Ghost]]. It is the first TV show to be produced by Williams Street, the company that would start up [[Adult Swim]] in the early 2000s.

It would inspire spin-offs in the form of Cartoon Planet, the Brak Show, [[Harvey Birdman: Attorney at Law]] (based on Space Ghost contemporary [[Birdman (series)|]]), and most famously, [[Aqua Teen Hunger Force]].

title: space_ghost_(series)
body:
Space Ghost is an American Saturday morning superhero cartoon produced by [[Hanna-Barbera]] Productions that aired from 1966 to 1967. In Japan, the cartoon aired on NET (now [[TV Asahi]]) in 1967, and would inspire two "manga":[https://spaceghost.fandom.com/wiki/Space_Ghost_(manga)] adaptations.

In the 1990s, [[Cartoon Network]] began airing [[Space Ghost Coast to Coast]], an adult animated comedy late-night talk show that used the art assets from the original series. It would inspire spin-offs in the form of Cartoon Planet, the Brak Show, [[Harvey Birdman: Attorney at Law]] (based on Space Ghost contemporary [[Birdman (series)|]]), and most famously, [[Aqua Teen Hunger Force]].

title: gerudo_set_(zelda)
body:
A disguise [[Link]] wears in order to infiltrate the [[Gerudo]] village in [[The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild]]. 

The outfit, like the rest of Gerudo attire, is [[arabian clothes]], with a [[veil]], [[detached sleeves]] and [[harem pants]]. Link wears a [[circlet]], [[armlet]]s and [[bridal gauntlets]], and a [[halterneck]] [[bandeau]] that shows off his [[bare shoulders]].

Link also has a male Gerudo set of clothing known as the [[Desert Voe Set (zelda)|]].

title: leo_(fire_emblem_fates)
body:
[b]Leo[/b] (レオン Reon) is a playable character in [i][[Fire Emblem Fates]][/i].

He is the younger prince of Nohr and a general of the kingdom's army. Unlike his older brother Xander, he uses magic. A master tactician, Leo is known for his keen intellect and sharp tongue. Along with the other royal siblings, he was subject to the family's "concubine wars" at a young age. He likes tomatoes the most out of anyone in the army, and his birthday is on June 30th.

He is voiced by [[Miyano Mamoru]] in Japanese and "Max Mittelman":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Mittelman in English.

[b]Xander[/b] (マークス, [i]Mākusu[/i]) is a playable character in [i][[Fire Emblem Fates]][/i].

The crown prince of the kingdom of Nohr. Xander has an aloof but dignified and courageous character, putting his country's needs above all else even at his own expense. Along with the other royal siblings, he was subject to the family's "concubine wars" at a young age. He is said to have the best handwriting out of those in the army, and his birthday is on October 27th.
